RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 17400. FOR REGISTERED OHIO FOALS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 20 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 20 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STRIKE ONE angled in from the six to the two path passing the five furlong marker, set a pressured pace into the stretch then widened the balance of the trip to win going away under a strong hand ride. BAILEY ROAD pressured the winner two wide into the stretch then was no match while well clear for second. AFLEET O ME was in tight between rivals causing his rider to check soon after the five eighths pole as the winner angled in then went evenly. OXBOW'S RIDE was in tight along the rail causing his rider to check just past the five eighths pole then failed to menace. KETTLE KING inched closer two wide on the turn then came up empty. THE STEWARDS POSTED THE INQUIRY SIGN AND THE RIDER OF OXBOW'S RIDE LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF THE WINNER FOR INTERFERENCE SOON AFTER THE START. AFTER REVIEW THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED STRIKE ONE AND PLACED HIM FOURTH.
